modules.description: Provides functions to retrieve and manipulate resource usage data for a thread, including user and system time, memory statistics, and context switches. Works with the `rusage` data structure and associated time values from the Unix module. Used to monitor performance metrics in real-time applications or debug resource-intensive operations.

Returns a record containing detailed CPU and memory usage metrics for a process or its terminated children. Includes user and system time, memory size, page faults, and context switches. Used to monitor performance and resource consumption of processes in system-level applications.
